Caramelized Pineapple Pudding
  --@wickdconfections
  
Base:
5 c brioche bread, 1" cubes (300 g)

Bake cubes at 300F / 150C for 12–18 min until dry. Cool.

Topping:
2 tbsp butter
3 tbsp brown sugar
1/4 c sliced almonds (30 g)
6–8 pineapple rings, drained very well

Pat pineapple very dry. Cook butter + brown sugar until bubbling. Caramelize rings 2–3 min per side. Remove. Toast almonds in remaining caramel. Remove.

Custard:
4 large eggs
3/4 c sugar (150 g)
1 1/4 c whole milk (300 ml)
4 tbsp unsalted butter, melted (56 g)
1 tsp vanilla extract
1/4 tsp salt
1/2 tsp cinnamon (optional)
pinch nutmeg (optional)
1 can crushed pineapple in juice (20 oz / 567 g), do not drain

Butter baking dish. Whisk eggs, sugar, salt. Whisk in milk, butter, vanilla, spices. Fold in brioche + crushed pineapple with juice. Let rest 15 min. Spread in dish. Top with caramelized pineapple. Bake 55–70 min until firm and golden.

Finish:
1 tbsp sugar

Sprinkle sugar over pineapple. Broil 1–3 min until bubbling. Cool 45–60 min before slicing. Top with toasted almonds and serve.

Notes: sweeter version - Use 1 c sugar in custard. Brush hot pudding with 2 tbsp melted butter + 2 tbsp brown sugar and broil until glossy.
